Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Using the same chain, for too long would just make it impractical to use... It would gget huge and finding the files in the chain would get slow.

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Maybe each poster could be a chain

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Oh

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: that was the idea yea... problem is hsoting all those chains

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Ok I see the problem

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: like it can be used for some cool stuff, but I;m not sure I can really make a platform out of it or anything. Definatly make a GUI that ppl can use top stream with though. if people find a use for it they can. We were thinkign on LABS to make a chain where we backup bootstraps into of chains that have ended.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Its an ondemand chain, so it only mines when you send files. The file needs to be stramed into the mining node aswell, the txs dont really propagate though the mempool, I think they are too fast....

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Maybe you're right though. Each file is a chain. But maybe the viewer mines it when wanting to view that file

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
No, the streamer mines the chain when they stream, and to veiw it you sync the chain, and issue an RPC call that pulls all the data in a block. 
The idea was for live video your GUI connects to the daemon, with -blocknotify and the data is automatically extracted and pushed to the app when a block arrives.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: that would feed into a video buffer

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: I see. Either way you got streaming to work. I saw your GitHub post a few days ago. Could lead to some other ideas

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Maybe not a YouTube type structure but more of a FB live structure

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: yeah the base of it is done, liek the algo that is needed, its very very fast. Did it all in C... Some of those loops and stuff I had to write are crazy, I'm not even sure how they work, but they do. üòÇ

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: for a couple of weeks work, without knowing like any C code it turned out pretty good.

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: Props man. If I ever get some more free time I will give it a go

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: no worries... I cant say when I will get back to it, hope its not too long. It was pretty fun.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: not 100% sure there is a working komodod fork where it actally works atm, but I have all the code on git.

Content: Roger that
